    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1447.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-18T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 14, 9 a.m. It is impossible for Receivership to make advances for a
                    greater sum than $5,000 daily.</p>
                <p>Department expects Jiménez and Velásquez to pledge themselves in writing to
                    recognize position of Comptroller and to turn over to Receivership collection of
                    internal revenues. In this way receipts and disbursements will be
                    controlled.</p>
                <p>Department regards it as essential that Johnston’s new budget shall not exceed
                    income.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
